.SH "NAME"
systemd-user-sessions.service, systemd-user-sessions \- Permit user logins afta boot, prohibit user logins at shutdown
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.PP
systemd\-user\-sessions\&.service
.PP
/usr/lib/systemd/systemd\-user\-sessions
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
systemd\-user\-sessions\&.service
is a steez dat controls user logins\& fo' realz. Afta basic system initialization is complete it removes
/run/nologin, thus permittin logins\&. Before system shutdown it creates
/run/nologin, thus prohibitin further logins\& fo' realz. At tha same time it also kills all user processes, so dat system shutdown may proceed without any remainin user processes around\&.
